tip.text: Calling it a gastro pub feels like a disservice. The food at this upscale but casual restaurant is fantastic! Plenty of choice for vegetarians on my visit. The 'liquid dessert' cocktails are great.
Very tasty Pad Thai!

formattedAddress: Kiosk on wheels, outside Brighton Stn. (Trafalgar St.)
location.address: Kiosk on wheels, outside Brighton Stn.

tip.text: Delicious, fresh Mexican flavours and this local gem. The nachos are amazing and their fresh salsa is very tasty. Try the cheese & pineapple quesadilla.
A better way to wait at Ibiza airport. It's peaceful with comfortable seating and reliable wifi. The food selection however is atrocious - much like the rest of the airport. They do have free booze.

formattedAddress: 07817 San Jose de la Atalaya Islas Baleares

tip.text: Friendly local cafe which serves great sandwiches at lunch time. I had the halloumi wrap which was delicious. Free wifi too.
A brilliant addition to the neighbourhood. Simple and delicious pizzas with light and fluffy, chewy bases, tasty toppings and an adventurous wine list. Relaxed and friendly, can't wait to go back.
Excellent food, really unique and totally delicious. I recommend the egg hopper. The curries to accompany them really pack a punch. Worth the long wait for a table.
Lovely bright and sunny spot with Brunch served all day. The Käse Spätzle with roast veg and a poached egg was great.
Dreadful and dreary.
Fantastic value! The pizza is delicious and you can fill up for under 5 €. Be prepared to queue for a table but your pizza will be ready in minutes. Mix and match slices to try them all.

Modern cafe with lots of cozy corners. Breakfast is a novel tick-box menu where you can create your own plate from a selection of breads, meats, cheese etc. Great coffee. Home made cakes look amazing!
Never been a huge fan of baked potatoes but I was blown away by the food here. Delicious ingredients in their extensive toppings make each potato a real treat. Lots for vegetarians here too.
Incredible food! The stack of hash browns with roasted aubergine is absolutely out of this world. Restaurant quality food in a relaxed cafe environment.
Very tasty food, better than the usual Vietnamese places in Berlin. We had the special: fried vegan duck in hoi sin sauce and it was delicious!
Great patio tables for a drink in the evening
The concept is a little dated and gimmicky but it's still fun to enter a 'secret' bar. The cocktails were pretty good, but the music was bad.

location.crossStreet: e/ Jorge Luis Borges y Thames
location.neighborhood: Palermo SoHo, Baires, Buenos Aires C.F.
formattedAddress: Costa Rica 4827 (e/ Jorge Luis Borges y Thames)

tip.text: Fine for a quick lunch but the pad Thai is far from authentic

venue.name: Estadio Alberto J. Armando "La Bombonera" (Club Atlético Boca Juniors)

tip.text: Go for sunset.

venue.name: Sugarloaf Mountain (Morro do Pão de Açúcar)

tip.text: Dinner on the beach. Good food, good wine and friendly service. They have vegetarian options that aren't listed on the menu, so just ask.
Paradise! We stayed in the honeymoon suite which was stunning with amazing views of the water and a huge terrace with comfy seats and a hammock. Staff are amazing and the food is great.
Probably one of the best restaurants in the Pelhourino. Good options for vegetarians

location.address: Largo Do Cruzeiro De São Francisco
formattedAddress: Largo Do Cruzeiro De São Francisco

tip.text: A great spot for a cocktail any time of the day.

location.address: Segunda Praia - Terrace on the very entrance
formattedAddress: Segunda Praia - Terrace on the very entrance

tip.text: Stunning! Great drinks from the bar too, friendly service.
Awful cattle pen.
Not your average Mexican restaurant. The dishes here are really creative, so forget guacamole & corn chips, and think BBQ Aubergine tacos and crisp fried Brussel sprouts with a spicy dip. Delicious!

location.crossStreet: Hackney Peace Carnival Mural, at 13 Dalston Ln.
formattedAddress: Dalston Ln. (Hackney Peace Carnival Mural, at 13 Dalston Ln.)

tip.text: Really stunning food. It might not look like much from the outside but this place is a must try in fhain. Regular changing menu. House wine is really good - and cheap!

contact.facebookName: The Household Cavalry Museum and Shop

tip.text: Brilliant burgers at this new joint in Kreuzberg. Big space featuring a cool bar, with plenty of seats. The veggie burger is great and the fries are amazing (big enough for two). Friendly staff too!
Highly recommended. Visit on Saturday afternoon for a free tour in English at 3pm. Our guide was amazing - knowledgable and enthusiastic. A brilliant experience.

venue.name: Berlin Ostkreuz Railway Station (Bahnhof Berlin Ostkreuz)

tip.text: Most Sundays throughout summer there will be parties here from midday. It's a great place to dance in the sunshine! During the week it becomes a chilled beer garden.

venue.name: Berlin Ostkreuz Railway Station (Bahnhof Berlin Ostkreuz)
Soviet War Memorial in Treptower Park (Sowjetisches Ehrenmal im Treptower Park)

formattedAddress: 07817 Sant Jordi de ses salines Islas Baleares

tip.text: Really great cozy restaurant serving a speciality dumpling, available in several different ways. It is REALLY delicious, and I can recommend the onion sauce (which is cooked for 13 hours). A must try!

venue.name: Berlin Ostkreuz Railway Station (Bahnhof Berlin Ostkreuz)

tip.text: Lovely place on the ground floor of Soho House. You can come and hang out at the bar or dive into the restaurant for amazing Italian food.
It's a lovely and stylish place to stay. Feels a little dated now but I think it's about to be returned. Make sure you book a bigger room with a balcony - there is a big difference!
A gorgeous place to hang out. The service on the beach is wonderful. Food throughout the house is excellent!
Came here for a pool party during MMW and it was a brilliant spot. Looks like a nice pool scene the rest of the year too. Free wifi.
$8 cocktails every day and a killer view at sunset

venue.name: Ocho Bar at SoHo Beach House

location.crossStreet: S. Priest Drive & W. Broadway Road
formattedAddress: 2100 S Priest Dr (S. Priest Drive & W. Broadway Road)

tip.text: One of the nicer Christmas markets in Berlin set against the stunning backdrop of the Schloss. They also had the best Kartoffelpuffer I've ever tried!
One of the best spots in Berlin on a sunny day. Great beach bar, good music and a super cool swimming pool (warning: the water is COLD!)
Nice spot on the river, but the wine is so-so and v. expensive.

formattedAddress: 11 West Riverwalk South (at N State St)

tip.text: Amazing breakfast spot! I'm vegetarian, and there are plenty of options - but I had a veggie version of the Bulls Eye French Toast...TRY IT!!
Nice spot for a drink on a sunny day. Wait for the wake boarders, and watch them fall in. Tee hee.
